"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWritten Evidence from the \nDepartment for Transport (WRT 012)\n&#xa0;\nQuestions&#xa0;How resilient are the \nUK\n’s transport networks (including road, rail and air) to adverse winter weather?\n&#xa0;\nWhat lessons have been learned since the severe weather experienced in the winter of 2009-10?  What practical changes have been made to ensure the \nUK\n is now better equipped to deal with severe weather?\n&#xa0;\nHow well prepared are the Government, local authoriti\nes and transport providers for adverse winter weather?  What more should be done to ensure a co-ordinated response?\n&#xa0;\nIntroduction&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Local Roads&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRoad Salt&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n(a) retaining a national strategic salt reserve of 425,000 tonnes and \nensuring that we have robust distribution procedures in place\n&#xa0;\n(b) publishing an updated note on the Department for Transport website (at end of each October) which provides local highway authorities with details on how to access the strategic salt stockpi\nle if it is required; and \n&#xa0;\n(c) continuing to monitor salt stocks of highway authorities across \nEngland\n, \nScotland\n and \nWales\n hold.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRail&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe industry has also implemented a comprehensive programme of actions to improve \npassenger information during disruption.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nAviation&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nMaritime&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nOctober 2013\n \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n \nThese include the Independent Review of England’s Transport System in Winter (2010) and the Transport Select Committee Report, ‘Keeping the UK Moving: The Impact on Transport of the Winter Weather in December 2010’.\n \n“Ploughing On – A \nreview of highway resilience in Winter 2013”\n"